Longest Common Subsequence (LCS) algorit.code:
```python
def lcs(xstr, ystr):
 n, m = len(xstr), len(ystr)
 dp = [[0]*(m+1) for _ in range(n+1)]
 for i in range(1, n+1):
  for j in range(1, m+1):
   if xstr[i-1] == ystr[j-1]:
    dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1] + 1
   else:
    dp[i][j] = max(dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1])
 return dp[n][m]
